Earlier device reports ([http://www.dd-wrt.com/phpBB2/viewtopic.php?t=70505 DD-WRT forum thread]) indicate that this device had a 128MB ''AOTOM'' A128168L-6TE RAM chip (perhaps [[ASUS RT-N10+|rev A]]?). Later revision models (B1, or at least some B1s) appear to have downgraded to the 32MB ''ESMT'' M12L2561616A-6T. The current trunk version of ''OpenWrt'' (r40730, RT-N10+ build) seems to work fine on this device. {{see also|ASUS RT-N10 rev B1|ASUS RT-N10 rev C1}} ===Bundled power suppl(y/ies)=== The included power supply is a '''RUIDE''' RD1200500-C55-8MG. :ID/OD measurements are approximate. {{hasPowerSupply |brand = RUIDE |model = RD1200500-C55-8MG |countrymanuf = China |input_v=100-240 |input_a=0.25 |input_c=AC |input_conn=NEMA 1-15P |output_v=12 |output_a=0.5 |output_conn=barrel |e_level=5 }} ==Links of Interest== *[https://www.asus.com/supportonly/RT-N10%20Plus%20(VER.B1)/HelpDesk_Download/ Downloads] (RT-N10 B1/RT-N10+ B1) ===Reviews=== *[http://www.foxnetwork.ru/index.php/component/content/article/119-asus-rt-g32-rev-c1-and-rt-n10-revb1.html ''ASUS RT-G32 rev.
